channel.title: How to change the F keys in your server? (PI Source)
channel.description: I am using a PI source which doesn't have the F keys that I would like to use, I would like to use the one that are in RuneScape, so that more people will want to hybrid. Can somebody please give me a tutorial or give me a link to a tutorial on how to code your F keys differently? I would greatly appreciate it

item.dc:creator: @hadesflames hadesflames
item.description:
@hadesflames wrote:

[quote=“ExtremeX-Scape™, post:4, topic:394026”][quote author=Arcane Mage link=topic=491213.msg3592169#msg3592169 date=1304732552]
I’m stupid, tell me what that means lol
[/quote]
No, you’re not stupid, you just want to be ‘spoon-fed’ how to do it, you’re never going to get anywhere in life, if you always have someone telling you exactly what to do, take some time& learn, it makes you feel good when you accomplish something that you thought you ‘couldn’t’ do.[/quote]

Damn right.

@op try googling to see how F keys work in java, and then search for that kind of code in your client. It’s not that hard to move things around at that point.
